headline: Realtor.com速: Seven Figures Is Not What It Used to Be - Luxury Now Starts at $1.3 Million
summary: A million-dollar home used to be the epitome of luxury, but Realtor.com速's new What is Luxury Report shows that the luxury threshold has risen from $796,922 in 2016 to about $1.3 million today. While a $1 million home was comfortably above the luxury bar in 2016, buyers now need to spend closer to $1.6 million to reach that same level of luxury status.
